.Im MicroEmacs filetype
.so me.tni
.TH haxe 9
.XI hx - "Haxe transpiler programming language"
.SH SYNOPSIS
hx \- Haxe transpiler programming language
.SH FILES
.na
.B hkhaxe.emf
\- Haxe programming language hook definition
.br
.B haxe.eaf
\- Haxe programming language abbreviation file
.br
.B haxe.etf
\- Haxe programming language template file
.ad
.SH EXTENSIONS
.na
\fB.hx\fR \- Haxe
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IP "\fBGeneral Editing\fR"
On creating a new file, a new header is automatically included into the file.
.Ht time 2m
is by default enabled, allowing the modification time-stamp to be maintained in
the header.
.IP "\fBHilighting\fR"
The  hilighting  features allow  commands,  variables,  logicals, comments,   
strings  and  characters  of  the  language  to  be
differentiated and rendered in different colors.
.IP "\fBAuto Layout\fR"
The command
.Ht indent 2
performs automatic layout of the text.
.IP
.Ht restyle-region 3
and
.Ht restyle-buffer 3
are available to reformat  (re-layout) selected sections of the buffer, or the
whole buffer, respectively.
.IP
Comments  may be formatted  using  \fC\*eo\fR,  which  reformats  the  comments
according  to  the  current  fill  paragraph.  If  a  comment  commences  with
\fC/***...\fR then the comment is automatically formatted to a box.
.IP "\fBFolding and Information Hiding\fR"
Generic  folding  is  enabled  within  the Haxe file. The folds  occur  about
functions,  classes, enums and interface  etc definition as long as they start
with a lowercase letter and and a final opening brace on that line and  a closing  
curly brace at the  beginning  of a line.
.Ht collapse-all 3
(un)folds all regions in the file,
.Ht collapse-current 3
(un)folds the current region.
.IP "\fBNavigation via Item List\fR"
The Haxe mode offers beside folding as well support for displaying an outline of the
functions, classes, enums, typedef and interface definitions of the Haxe file for easy navigation using the 
.Ht item-list 3
.IP "\fBAbbreviations\fR"
The  installation  comes with a default  abbreviation  file for Haxe file  editing
which  can  be  used  by  writing  short   abbreviations   like   "\fBfo\fR" (for),
"\fBif\fR", "\fBei\fR" (else if) or "\fBcl\fR" (class) - and then pressing the key-binding for the 
.Ht expand-abbrev-handle 3
command.  The  list  of  abbreviations  can be used  interactively  in the GUI
version of \*(mS using the 
.Ht abbrev-list 3
command.
.IP "\fBWorking Environment\fR"
.Ht compile 3
may be invoked to rebuild the source, the user is prompted to save any files.
.IP "\fBShort Cuts\fR"
The short cut keys used within the buffer are:
.IP
\fB\*cc \*cc\fR \- Comment out the current line.
.br
\fB\*cc \*cd\fR \- Uncomment the current line.
.br
\fB\*cc \*ce\fR \- Comment to the end of the line with stars (*).
.br
\fB\*a\*ci\fR \- Restyle the current region.
.br
\fB\*eq\fR \- Format a comment.
.br
\fB\*eo\fR \- Format a comment.
.br
\fBf2\fR \- (Un)fold the current region.
.br
\fB\*cf2\fR \- (Un)fold all regions.
.br
\fBf6\fR \- List items.
.br
\fB\*ef6\fR \- Close item list,
.SH NOTES
.PP
The  hilighting  or the addition of new item list matches  is  typically
extended  using  a  file   \fBmyhaxe.emf\fR
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
.Ht abbrev-list 3 ,
.Ht collapse-all 3 ,
.Ht collapse-current 3 ,
.Ht compile 3 ,
.Ht expand-abbrev-handle 3 ,
.Ht item-list 3 ,
.Ht restyle-buffer 3 ,
.Ht restyle-region 3 ,
.Ht time 2m .
.sp 1
.Hl "Supported File Types" FileTypes -
.ad
.FH
